    • Method Detail

      • createNewBucketEntry

        protected BucketEntry createNewBucketEntry(int bucketNumber,
                                           VaultEntry entry)
        This method creates a new BucketEntry out of the given int and VaultEntry. The int is the consecutive numbering of the BucketEntry. During the process the VaultEntryType will be checked and all necessary inputs for the arrays inside the BucketEntry will be generated accordingly. The generated information inside the BucketEntry does not contain the information of other BucketEntrys needed for further processing.
        Parameters:
        bucketNumber - The consecutive number of the BucketEntry that is being created.
        entry - The VaultEntry that will be stored inside the BucketEntry.
        Returns:
        This method returns a newly created BucketEntry

      • createEmptyBucketEntry

        protected BucketEntry createEmptyBucketEntry(int bucketNumber,
                                             java.util.Date date)
                                      throws java.text.ParseException
        This method creates a new empty BucketEntry out of the given int and Date. The int is the consecutive numbering of the BucketEntry. A new VaultEntry will be created containing the VauleEntryType EMPTY and the given Date.
        Parameters:
        bucketNumber - The consecutive number of the BucketEntry that is being created.
        date - The Date (timestamp) that is needed to create a vaild VaultEntry
        Returns:
        This method returns an newly created 'empty' BucketEntry.
        Throws:
        java.text.ParseException

      • recreateBucketEntry

        protected BucketEntry recreateBucketEntry(BucketEntry oldBucketEntry)
        This method gets a BucketEntry and creates a new BucketEntry with the same information.
        Parameters:
        oldBucketEntry - This is the BucketEntry that will be recreated.
        Returns:
        The method returns the recreated BucketEntry.
